   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>B. Jehovah's Judgment</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>In Isaiah 29:1-12, 14-16 we see Jehovah's judgment on the hypocrisy of the worshippers in Jerusalem.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Jehovah Distressing Ariel</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>According to verses 2 through 8, Jehovah will distress Israel.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The nations will fight against her and her stronghold.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Jehovah Pouring Out</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>upon Them a Spirit of Deep Sleep,</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>and Shutting Their Eyes, the Prophets,</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>and Covering Their Heads, the Seers</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Verse 9 says that they are drunk, but not with wine; they stagger, but not with liquor.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Jehovah has poured out upon them a spirit of deep sleep and has shut their eyes, the prophets; and their heads, the seers, He has covered v. 10 . All the vision will be to them like the words of a book that has been sealed vv.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>11-12 .</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The Lord Doing Something Wondrous with Them</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Verse 14 tells us that the Lord will do something wondrous with them, something wondrously marvelous; and the wisdom of their wise men will perish, and the understanding of those who understand will be hidden.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Verses 15 and 16 go on to say, "Woe to those who hide deeply/Their counsel from Jehovah,/And whose deeds are in the dark/And who say, Who sees us? and, Who knows us?/You turn things upside down!/Shall the potter be considered to be like the clay,/ That what is made should say to him who made it, He did not make me,/Or what is formed should say to him who formed it, He has no understanding?"</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>These verses reveal that the hypocritical worshippers were in darkness and were without wisdom.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>They had even turned things upside down.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>C. Issuing In the Restoration</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Jehovah's judgment on the hypocrisy of Jerusalem's worshippers issues in the restoration vv.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>17-24 .</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Lebanon Being Turned into a Fruitful Field</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>In the restoration, Lebanon will be turned into a fruitful field, and the fruitful field will be considered to be a forest v. 17 . This indicates that Lebanon will be flourishing.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The Deaf Hearing the Words of the Book</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The deaf will hear the words of the book, and out of gloom and darkness the eyes of the blind will see v. 18 .</S>
   </TEXT>
